1 AN ACT relating to membership of the Geographic Information Advisory Council.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 ïƒ¢Section 1. KRS 42.740 is amended to read as follows:
4 (1) There is hereby established a Geographic Information Advisory Council, attached
5 to the Commonwealth Office of Technology for administrative purposes, to advise
6 the executive director of the Commonwealth Office of Technology on issues
7 relating to geographic information and geographic information systems.
8 (2) The council shall recommend policies and procedures that assist state and local
9 jurisdictions in developing, deploying, and leveraging geographic information
10 resources and geographic information systems technology for the purpose of
11 improving public administration.
12 (3) The council shall closely coordinate with users of geographic information systems
13 to recommend policies and procedures that ensure the maximum use of geographic
14 information by minimizing the redundancy of geographic information and
15 geographic information resources, as well as to ensure that the geographic
16 information clearinghouse maintained by the Division of Geographic Information
17 Systems meets the needs of all state agencies.
18 (4) (a) The Geographic Information Advisory Council shall consist of twenty-five
19 (25) members and one (1) legislative liaison. The members shall be
20 knowledgeable in the use and application of geographic information systems
21 technology and shall have sufficient authority within their organizations to
22 influence the implementation of council recommendations.
23 (b) The council shall consist of:
24 1. The secretary of the Transportation Cabinet or his or her designee;
25 2. The secretary of the Cabinet for Health and Family Services or his or
26 her designee;
27 3. The director of the Kentucky Geological Survey or his or her designee;
