2 (5) The council may have committees and subcommittees as determined by the council
3 or an executive committee, if an executive committee exists.
4 (6) A member of the council shall not:
5 (a) Be an officer, employee, or paid consultant of a business entity that has, or of
6 a trade association for business entities that have, a substantial interest in the
7 geographic information industry and is doing business in the Commonwealth;
8 (b) Own, control, or have, directly or indirectly, more than ten percent (10%)
9 interest in a business entity that has a substantial interest in the geographic
10 information industry;
11 (c) Be in any manner connected with any contract or bid for furnishing any
12 governmental body of the Commonwealth with geographic information
13 systems, the computers on which they are automated, or a service related to
14 geographic information systems;
15 (d) Be a person required to register as a lobbyist because of activities for
16 compensation on behalf of a business entity that has, or on behalf of a trade
17 association of business entities that have, substantial interest in the geographic
18 information industry;
19 (e) Accept or receive money or another thing of value from an individual, firm, or
20 corporation to whom a contract may be awarded, directly or indirectly, by
21 rebate, gift, or otherwise; or
22 (f) Be liable to civil action or any action performed in good faith in the
23 performance of duties as a council member.
24 (7) Those council members specified in subsection (4)(b)[(a)] of this section who serve
25 by virtue of an office shall serve on the board while they hold that office.
26 (8) Appointed members of the council shall serve for a term of four (4) years.
27 Vacancies in the membership of the council shall be filled in the same manner as
